      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Maple Leafs' season-long slide hit rock bottom two nights ago in Dallas, where they coughed up a late lead for a <strong>5-6 gut-punch loss to the Stars</strong>, extending their skid to six straight and burying them deeper in the playoff graveyard. Sitting at 32-35-14 with 78 points, eighth in the Atlantic and 35 games back, Toronto's long eliminated&mdash;playoff seed 15, clinched for the draft lottery. William Nylander's been grinding with 27 goals away from home, but the team's defense has imploded, hemorrhaging 21 goals across four defeats since the Islanders clipped them 3-5. No hot hands, just cold reality: this crew's playing for pride and ping-pong balls, their first-rounder owed to Boston unless it cracks the top five&mdash;they're hovering fifth now, but a win tonight drops them to sixth. Every shift matters in the final stretch, even if it's just to salvage draft position. <strong>Watch the Sens at 6:30 PM ET&mdash;Ottawa's locked as WC2, but Toronto needs points to hold the lottery line before Thursday's finale.</strong> The urgency's real; rebuild whispers grow louder by the hour.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
