      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Vladimir Guerrero Jr. ripped a go-ahead RBI double in the 10th, igniting the Toronto Blue Jays to a <strong>wild 9-7 extra-innings escape over the Brewers</strong> last night in Milwaukee &mdash; a gritty gut-check win that snapped their slide and breathed life into a 7-9 start lurking fourth in the AL East, three games back with that fragile one-game streak. After dropping four of five, including a Twin Cities beatdown, Vladdy's clutch rip &mdash; part of an insane back-and-forth &mdash; silenced the doubters, even as the rotation nurses fresh wounds that handed the Jays a golden shot at stability. No major Blue Jays injuries surfaced, but Guerrero's heroics masked the bullpen's wobbles, while the lineup clawed back from early deficits like the scrappers they've always been. At 7-9, they're no juggernaut yet &mdash; Rays lead at 9-7 &mdash; but this road trip tests their spine. <strong>Tonight's rubber match at 6:40 PM ET sends Dylan Cease to the hill against Jacob Misiorowski</strong>; snag a series win, and the hunt sharpens &mdash; falter, and the East's wolves close in.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
