      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Raptors",
        "body": "The Raptors' war room hums with quiet urgency this offseason&mdash;Toronto plotting a retool around their <strong>5th playoff seed from last spring's 46-36 finish, third in the Atlantic, now fueling a roster rebuild that demands bold strokes</strong>. Whispers from the past 48 hours point to front-office scouts zeroing in on trade targets to pair with Scottie Barnes, the 24-year-old cornerstone whose All-NBA flashes last year scream franchise savior, even as free agency looms with cap space to chase a rim protector. No splashy deals yet, but the machine grinds: draft lottery odds sharpen, summer league beckons, and training camp's horizon sharpens the focus on depth at the wings. Barnes' growth&mdash;averaging north of 20-8 last go-round&mdash;anchors it all, but without a co-star, the ceiling stays glass. Fans, exhale the playoff ghosts; this is reset mode, pure and simple. <strong>Watch the draft lottery ping-pong balls next month&mdash;they could vault Toronto into the top five picks and ignite a new contender's dawn</strong>.",
