      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The draft smoke's thickening around Washington like a D.C. fog bank, with the Commanders perched at No. 7 after a grim 5-12 slog that left them third in the NFC East, nine games back and staring down a roster rebuild. <strong>GM Adam Peters just wrapped visits with wideouts Carnell Tate, Makai Lemon, and Omar Cooper Jr.</strong> &mdash; a clear signal they're hunting firepower opposite Terry McLaurin, even as buzz swirls on QB backups like Jalon Daniels or Day 3 gems to groom behind Jayden Daniels. Free-agent grab Nick Cross bolsters the secondary alongside Will Harris, but safety's no lock, and mock drafts peg edge rushers or versatile receivers high on the board. Trade whispers? Peters, the ex-49ers wizard, could wheel and deal that seventh pick for volume or slide back if a blue-chip WR tumbles. Jayden Daniels remains the franchise spark, his legs still a nightmare for defenses, but the receiver drought hampers his arm. <strong>Eight days to Pittsburgh's green room</strong> &mdash; will they pounce on Tate's speed or flip the script? This pick reboots the contention window.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
